tegory><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Will Shanklin]]></category><media:content height="933" medium="image" url="https://o.aolcdn.com/images/dims?image_uri=https%3A%2F%2Fs.yimg.com%2Fos%2Fcreatr-uploaded-images%2F2023-12%2F956cb290-92ec-11ee-bf9b-c90cf8985f2b&amp;resize=1400%2C933&amp;client=19f2b5e49a271b2bde77&amp;signature=d216e85314e7b3bcd799c16f7e61db0ff6196411" width="1400"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="933" medium="image" url="https://o.aolcdn.com/images/dims?image_uri=https%3A%2F%2Fmedia-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fcreatr-uploaded-images%2F2023-12%2F956cb290-92ec-11ee-bf9b-c90cf8985f2b&amp;resize=1400%2C933&amp;client=19f2b5e49a271b2bde77&amp;signature=15a1c4930783ceff9cc57032b0028307ad912f9c" width="1400"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Photo by Billy Steele / Engadget]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[Photo of the Sony WH-1000XM5 headphones in silver sitting on a pile of colorful books.]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[Sony WH-1000XM5 headphones]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[Meta is disconnecting Messenger and Instagram chat later this month]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p> Meta 很快就会<a data-i13n="elm:context_link;elmt:doNotAffiliate;cpos:1;pos:1" class="no-affiliate-link" href="https://help.instagram.com/654906392080948" data-original-link="https://help.instagram.com/654906392080948">删除</a>一项可让您在 Instagram 上与 Facebook 好友聊天的功能。从 12 月中旬开始，该公司将断开<a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/facebook-chat-across-instagram-and-messenger-120049504.html">2020 年添加的</a>跨平台集成。它没有提供这样做的理由，但正如<em>9to5Google</em> <a data-i13n="elm:context_link;elmt:doNotAffiliate;cpos:3;pos:1" class="no-affiliate-link" href="https://9to5google.com/2023/12/04/instagram-facebook-messenger-chats-disconnected/" data-original-link="https://9to5google.com/2023/12/04/instagram-facebook-messenger-chats-disconnected/">推测的</a>那样，避免欧盟的监管后果听起来像是一个合乎逻辑的动机。</p><p>可选的跨平台集成<a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/2019-04-30-facebook-will-let-users-chat-across-messenger-instagram-and-wha.html">于 2019 年宣布</a>，一年后上线，模糊了该公司最受欢迎的两项服务之间的界限。 Messenger 副总裁 Loredena Crisan 当时表示：“就像今天，如果你有 Yahoo 帐户，你就可以与 Gmail 帐户对话，这些帐户将能够通过 Messenger 共享协议相互对话。”</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p> Meta 表示，一旦“2023 年 12 月中旬”到来，您将无法再通过 Instagram 与 Facebook 好友发起新的聊天或通话。如果您在 Instagram 上与 Facebook 帐户有任何现有对话，它们将变为只读。此外，Facebook 帐户将无法再查看您的活动状态或查看已读收据。最后，与 Facebook 帐户的任何现有聊天都不会移动到这两个平台上的收件箱。</p><p>欧盟设计了具有里程碑意义的《数字市场法案》，该法案于 2022 年通过，旨在<a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/european-union-digital-markets-services-acts-131818075.html">威慑平台持有者</a>获得垄断权力（或类似权力）。如果一家公司<a data-i13n="cpos:6;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/tech-giant-gatekeepers-must-comply-with-all-of-the-eus-new-digital-market-rules-065324264.html">超过了收入门槛</a>，并且欧盟委员会认为该平台过度占据主导地位，则最高可处以其上一年全球总营业额 10% 的罚款。鉴于这为管理机构提供了强制执行“大棒”，也许 Meta 看到了不祥之兆，并认为 Instagram/Facebook 交叉消息功能不值得冒险。</p>本文最初发表在 Engadget 上：https://www.engadget.com/meta-is-disconnecting-messenger-and-instagram-chat-later-this-month-205956880.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/meta-is-disconnecting-messenger-and-instagram-chat-later-this-month-205956880.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 2401ec67-01a6-4f91-b149-389c860ee915</guid><dc:creator>威尔·尚克林</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Mon, 04 Dec 2023 20:59:56 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1701723596</ingested><modified> 2023-12-04T21:00:01+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Personal Investing Ideas & Strategies]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Will Shanklin]]></category><media:content height="683" medium="image" url="https://o.aolcdn.com/images/dims?image_uri=https%3A%2F%2Fs.yimg.com%2Fos%2Fcreatr-uploaded-images%2F2023-12%2Fb978eca0-92e5-11ee-b77e-586782e6b789&amp;resize=1400%2C683&amp;client=19f2b5e49a271b2bde77&amp;signature=d89428ab6ddf9b077f2f7c0815ba7ea8630f8495" width="1400"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="683" medium="image" url="https://o.aolcdn.com/images/dims?image_uri=https%3A%2F%2Fmedia-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fcreatr-uploaded-images%2F2023-12%2Fb978eca0-92e5-11ee-b77e-586782e6b789&amp;resize=1400%2C683&amp;client=19f2b5e49a271b2bde77&amp;signature=62310db3848025561c548f677b6eb8dc3a0f3de1" width="1400"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Meta]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[Promotional image from Meta, showing for phones with chat screens between Facebook and Instagram.]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[Meta cross-app chat]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[ChatGPT says that asking it to repeat words forever is a violation of its terms]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p>上周，一组研究人员发表了一篇论文，表明通过要求 ChatGPT“永远”重复单词，它能够<a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/a-silly-attack-made-chatgpt-reveal-real-phone-numbers-and-email-addresses-200546649.html"><ins>无意中泄露</ins></a>一些数据，包括人们的电话号码、电子邮件地址和出生日期。 。根据<em>404 Media</em>和 Engadget 自己测试的<a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://www.404media.co/asking-chatgpt-to-repeat-words-forever-is-now-a-terms-of-service-violation/"><ins>报告</ins></a>，现在这样做违反了 ChatGPT 的服务条款。</p><p> “此内容可能违反我们的内容政策或使用条款”，ChatGPT 回应 Engadget 的提示时永远重复“你好”一词。 “如果您认为这是错误的，请提交您的反馈——您的意见将有助于我们在这一领域的研究。”</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p>然而， <em>404 Media</em>指出，OpenAI 的 <a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://openai.com/policies/usage-policies?ref=404media.co"><ins>内容政策</ins></a>中没有任何语言禁止用户要求服务永远重复单词。在“ <a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://openai.com/policies/mar-2023-terms?ref=404media.co"><ins>使用条款</ins></a>”下，OpenAI 声明用户不得“使用任何自动化或编程方法从服务中提取数据或输出”，但仅仅提示 ChatGPT 永远重复单词并不是自动化或编程。 OpenAI 没有回应 Engadget 的置评请求。</p><p>聊天机器人的行为揭开了现代人工智能服务所依赖的训练数据的面纱。批评者指责 OpenAI 等公司在未经拥有这些数据的人同意的情况下，使用互联网上的大量可用数据来构建 ChatGPT 等专有产品，也没有向他们提供补偿。</p>本文最初发表在 Engadget 上：https://www.engadget.com/chatgpt-says-that-asking-it-to-repeat-words-forever-is-a-violation-of-its-terms-202622018.html ?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/chatgpt-says-that-asking-it-to-repeat-words-forever-is-a-violation-of-its-terms-202622018.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 2472c767-d732-4db2-a9df-d418104dd1ab</guid><dc:creator>普拉纳夫·迪克西特,普拉纳夫·迪克西特</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Mon, 04 Dec 2023 20:26:22 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1701721583</ingested><modified> 2023-12-04T20:26:28+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Pranav Dixit]]></category><media:content height="958" medium="image" url="https://o.aolcdn.com/images/dims?image_uri=https%3A%2F%2Fs.yimg.com%2Fos%2Fcreatr-uploaded-images%2F2023-12%2Fd24813e0-92e1-11ee-9bd4-113f23176cf0&amp;resize=1400%2C958&amp;client=19f2b5e49a271b2bde77&amp;signature=83cb5be7e98953533ff4001442c6d1b18823cfc5" width="1400"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="958" medium="image" url="https://o.aolcdn.com/images/dims?image_uri=https%3A%2F%2Fmedia-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fcreatr-uploaded-images%2F2023-12%2Fd24813e0-92e1-11ee-9bd4-113f23176cf0&amp;resize=1400%2C958&amp;client=19f2b5e49a271b2bde77&amp;signature=02b8060ee8ee6a9745cf27d3f35a1a787d117a7d" width="1400"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Aaron Souppouris]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[Asking ChatGPT to repeat a word "forever" now results in a terms of service violation message.]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ChatGPT TOS violation screenshot]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[Verizon subscribers can get Netflix and Max for $10 a month]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p> Verizon 周一<a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Verizon;elmt:;cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=2225d53b-bfe1-4d56-bd6e-3885c642b140&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Verizon&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsImxhbmRpbmdVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL3d3dy52ZXJpem9uLmNvbS9hYm91dC9uZXdzL3Zlcml6b24tb2ZmZXItbmV0ZmxpeC1tYXgtc3RyZWFtaW5nLWJ1bmRsZS0xMC1tb250aC1teXBsYW4tcGVyayIsImNvbnRlbnRVdWlkIjoiZTgyMmM1NDMtZTEwOC00MjQ4LThkYzEtMTQ2ODczMjJmNTc5In0&amp;signature=AQAAAY9cusup67DwNmF4FSex7tgqf_Fdh1iy7KQfuI1BBnhr&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.verizon.com%2Fabout%2Fnews%2Fverizon-offer-netflix-max-streaming-bundle-10-month-myplan-perk" class="rapid-with-clickid" data-original-link="https://www.verizon.com/about/news/verizon-offer-netflix-max-streaming-bundle-10-month-myplan-perk">证实，</a>它将提供<a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/verizon-may-soon-offer-a-10-bundle-of-netflix-and-max-ad-supported-plans-174029656.html">先前传闻的</a>Netflix 和 Max 流媒体订阅捆绑包。竞争对手服务的配对在同类服务中尚属首次，与单独购买这两个广告支持的计划相比，该无线运营商的 myPlan 订户可享受 41% 的折扣。该优惠将于 12 月 7 日开始提供。</p><p>该捆绑包将包括<a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/netflix-basic-with-ads-explainer-190555318.html">广告支持的 Netflix</a>和<a data-i13n="elm:context_link;elmt:doNotAffiliate;cpos:4;pos:1" class="no-affiliate-link" href="https://www.engadget.com/max-hbo-max-rebrand-analysis-194800553.html" data-original-link="https://www.engadget.com/max-hbo-max-rebrand-analysis-194800553.html">Max</a>套餐，每月费用为 10 美元。这些级别的费用通常分别为每月 6.99 美元和 9.99 美元，因此，与直接从服务网站支付的费用相比，获得该优惠的客户每年可以节省 80 美元。对于 Netflix 和华纳兄弟探索频道来说，这是一个增加订户数量并让更多人迷上独家剧集的机会。与此同时，Verizon 还获得了从竞争对手运营商那里吸引客户的另一个动力。</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p>只有 Verizon 的 myPlan 客户才有资格获得 10 美元的流媒体捆绑包。该运营商提供三个级别的 myPlan，起价为每月 75 美元（单用户），无限欢迎。 Unlimited Plus 级别将单行价格推至每月 90 美元，而 Unlimited Ultimate 价格为每月 100 美元。您的计划中的用户越多，所有三个级别提供的每线价格就越低。您可以访问<a data-i13n="elm:context_link;elmt:doNotAffiliate;cpos:5;pos:1" class="no-affiliate-link" href="https://www.verizon.com/plans/unlimited/" data-original-link="https://www.verizon.com/plans/unlimited/">Verizon 的 myPlan 网站</a>了解完整的详细信息。</p><p> Verizon 还有其他几项 10 美元流媒体交易作为 myPlan 附加服务。其中包括<a data-i13n="elm:context_link;elmt:doNotAffiliate;cpos:6;pos:1" class="no-affiliate-link" href="https://www.verizon.com/solutions-and-services/add-ons/entertainment/disney-bundle-perk/" data-original-link="https://www.verizon.com/solutions-and-services/add-ons/entertainment/disney-bundle-perk/">Disney Bundle</a> ，它结合了 Disney+、带广告的 Hulu 和 ESPN+。它还提供<a data-i13n="elm:context_link;elmt:doNotAffiliate;cpos:7;pos:1" class="no-affiliate-link" href="https://www.verizon.com/solutions-and-services/add-ons/entertainment/apple-one/" data-original-link="https://www.verizon.com/solutions-and-services/add-ons/entertainment/apple-one/">Apple One 捆绑包</a>，包括 Apple Music、Apple TV+、Apple Arcade 和 iCloud+。 <em>Variety</em> <a data-i13n="elm:context_link;elmt:doNotAffiliate;cpos:8;pos:1" class="no-affiliate-link" href="https://variety.com/2023/digital/news/verizon-bundle-netflix-max-ads-price-1235820291/" data-original-link="https://variety.com/2023/digital/news/verizon-bundle-netflix-max-ads-price-1235820291/">指出</a>，像 Verizon 这样的无线运营商通常会按每个用户的批发费率向服务提供商支付费用，并将这些成本视为客户获取开销。</p><p>除了 myPlan 注册之外，此优惠还要求您年满 18 岁才能注册。选择附加组件后，您需要为每项服务分别完成帐户设置。</p>本文最初发表在 Engadget 上：https://www.engadget.com/verizon-subscribers-can-get-netflix-and-max-for-10-a-month-200120804.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/verizon-subscribers-can-get-netflix-and-max-for-10-a-month-200120804.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> e822c543-e108-4248-8dc1-14687322f579</guid><dc:creator>威尔·尚克林</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Mon, 04 Dec 2023 20:01:20 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1701720081</ingested><modified> 2023-12-04T20:01:25+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Will Shanklin]]></category><media:content height="864" medium="image" url="https://o.aolcdn.com/images/dims?image_uri=https%3A%2F%2Fs.yimg.com%2Fos%2Fcreatr-uploaded-images%2F2023-12%2F928d2530-92df-11ee-bf3d-6bf415063b02&amp;resize=1400%2C864&amp;client=19f2b5e49a271b2bde77&amp;signature=c1682503e447303d2013169887ff4542f6173be1" width="1400"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="864" medium="image" url="https://o.aolcdn.com/images/dims?image_uri=https%3A%2F%2Fmedia-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fcreatr-uploaded-images%2F2023-12%2F928d2530-92df-11ee-bf3d-6bf415063b02&amp;resize=1400%2C864&amp;client=19f2b5e49a271b2bde77&amp;signature=fc6b2057f773a5443a26b553eff6c1988279fb04" width="1400"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Verizon]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[Netflix Max Verizon deal]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[Netflix Max Verizon deal]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[TikTok's Ticketmaster integration expands to users outside the US]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p>早在 8 月份，TikTok 就与 Ticketmaster 合作， <a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/tiktok-ticketmaster-event-tickets-161351915.html"><ins>允许艺术家直接通过社交媒体应用程序出售现场活动的门票</ins></a>。然而，到目前为止，这项服务仅限于美国。 TikTok 刚刚宣布<a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://newsroom.tiktok.com/en-us/tiktok-and-ticketmaster-expand-partnership-across-more-than-20-countries"><ins>与 Ticketmaster 的合作关系除澳大利亚和英国外，现已扩展到</ins></a>北美和欧洲的 20 多个国家。</p><p>该工具仅适用于经该平台官方认证的艺术家，尽管 TikTok 表示该艺术家和活动提供商已超过 75,000 名。功能很简单。艺术家在视频中嵌入了相关 Ticketmaster 活动的链接。用户单击屏幕左下角的链接并购买门票，但我们鼓励潜在买家<a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/live-nation-and-ticketmaster-to-start-showing-hidden-ticket-costs-170552346.html"><ins>留意这些隐藏费用。</ins></a></p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p>音乐是这里的主要动力，但您也可以买到喜剧表演、体育赛事以及其他类型的娱乐活动的门票。 TikTok 宣称，该计划已经为仙妮亚·唐恩 (Shania Twain)、伯纳·男孩 (Burna Boy)、The Kooks 等艺术家的成功票务活动提供了支持，并表示，自此以来，利用应用内票务功能的视频观看次数已超过 25 亿次。发射。</p><p>该工具现已可供居住在瑞典、瑞士、波兰等约 17 个新符合条件的国家/地区的人们使用。 TikTok 尚未宣布未来是否会开设更多地点，但一位发言人表示，该公司“非常高兴看到与 Ticketmaster 的合作关系将如何随着时间的推移而发展。”</p><p> Snapchat <a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/snapchat-live-concerts-ticketmaster-123016106.html"><ins>去年也采取了类似的举措，</ins></a>与 Ticketmaster 合作，为用户匹配附近的现场音乐会。然而，TikTok 的方法更加简化，应该可以更快地获取门票。</p>本文最初发表在 Engadget 上：https://www.engadget.com/tiktoks-ticketmaster-integration-expands-to-users-outside-the-us-182324778.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/tiktoks-ticketmaster-integration-expands-to-users-outside-the-us-182324778.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 20dcf280-d82c-49a4-8d14-1ecae619d62a</guid><dc:creator>劳伦斯·邦克</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Mon, 04 Dec 2023 18:23:24 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1701713612</ingested><modified> 2023-12-04T18:13:36+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Small Businesses]]></category><category><![CDATA[Media]]></category><category><![CDATA[Arts & Entertainment Tickets]]></category><category><![CDATA[Arts & Entertainment Events]]></category><category><![CDATA[Arts & Entertainment]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Lawrence Bonk]]></category><media:content height="813" medium="image" url="https://o.aolcdn.com/images/dims?image_uri=https%3A%2F%2Fs.yimg.com%2Fos%2Fcreatr-uploaded-images%2F2023-12%2F4619a1e0-92cd-11ee-bd5d-1e35052b1a57&amp;resize=1400%2C813&amp;client=19f2b5e49a271b2bde77&amp;signature=3d0fbb3802084fd2b71f14262e35959abf635872" width="1400"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="813" medium="image" url="ht